com.iopipe

Class IOpipeExecution

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.iopipe.IOpipeExecution

  • public final class IOpipeExecution
extends Object
    This class provides access to information and functionality which is specific to a single execution of a method. Each execution will have a unique instance of this object and as such will be initialized when it is first used.
    Since:
    2018/01/19

      • plugin

        public final <C extends IOpipePluginExecution,R extends AutoCloseable,V> R plugin(Class<C> __cl,
                                                                                  BiFunction<C,V,R> __func,
                                                                                  V __v)
                                                                           throws ClassCastException,
                                                                                  NullPointerException
        This searches for the specified plugin if the plugin exists it will return an instance of AutoCloseable which may be used with try-with-resources. An optional secondary argument may be passed to simplify some operations that take an extra parameter.
        Type Parameters:
        C - The class type of the execution state.
        R - The type of object to return.
        V - The type of extra value to pass to the function.
        Parameters:
        __cl - The class object of the execution state.
        __func - The function to obtain the AutoCloseable for use with try-with-resources for.
        __v - The extra value to be passed to the function.
        Returns:
        The A object or null if the plugin is not valid or no value was returned.
        Throws:
        ClassCastException - If the class type is not valid.
        NullPointerException - On null arguments except for __v.
        Since:
        2018/01/23

                                                         throws ClassCastException,
